
1. Power Distribution (Assuming a 5V BEC from an ESC or PDB)

5V Source ➔ ESP32-S3 5V pin

5V Source ➔ FlySky Receiver VCC (or 5V) pin

Main Ground ➔ ESP32-S3 GND pin

Main Ground ➔ FlySky Receiver GND pin

Main Ground ➔ MPU6500 GND pin

Main Ground ➔ All 4 ESC GND pins (signal ground)

2. MPU-6500 Sensor (I2C Connection)

MPU6500 VCC ➔ ESP32-S3 3.3V pin (Important: Use 3.3V, not 5V, to prevent damage)

MPU6500 GND ➔ ESP32-S3 GND pin

MPU6500 SCL ➔ ESP32-S3 SCL pin (Typically GPIO 9 on the SuperMini, or your defined I2C SCL)

MPU6500 SDA ➔ ESP32-S3 SDA pin (Typically GPIO 8 on the SuperMini, or your defined I2C SDA)

3. Motors / ESC Signals (Based on your configuration parameters)

ESC 1 Signal ➔ ESP32-S3 GPIO 1 (from set pin_output_0 1)

ESC 2 Signal ➔ ESP32-S3 GPIO 2 (from set pin_output_1 2)

ESC 3 Signal ➔ ESP32-S3 GPIO 10 (from set pin_output_2 10)

ESC 4 Signal ➔ ESP32-S3 GPIO 13 (from set pin_output_3 13)

4. FlySky Receiver (3-Pin PWM protocal)

Receiver VCC ➔ 5V Source

Receiver GND ➔ Main Ground

Receiver Signal ➔ gpio 12 
